<Content>
<![CDATA[
<html>
  <head>
    <title>A strange harmonic oscillator</title>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>
      A strange harmonic oscillator
    </h1>
    Two equal masses are tied up by means of a light rigid rod and may move 
    without friction along two perpendicular rails in a horizontal table.<br>The 
    unit length has be chosen equal to the rod length and the unit mass equal 
    to the total mass of the system.
  </body>
</html>

]]>

</Content>
</Osejs.Description.Page>
<Osejs.Description.Page>
<Type>DESCRIPTION_EDITOR</Type>
<Name>Activities</Name>
<Active>true</Active>
<Content>
<![CDATA[
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Activities</title>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <h2>
      Activities
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Choose the right generalized coordinate to write the conservation law 
        of the mechanical energy. Which kind of motion will describe each 
        particle?
      </li>
      <li>
        Check your guess by enabling <b>Graph</b>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use your analytical calculation to show that each mass motion is 
        harmonic but rather unusual, since the oscillation period depends on 
        the energy in a precise way you have to find.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use the simulation to check (qualitatively and quantitatively) the 
        last result.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>

]]>

</Content>
